{{Taoism}}
'''[[Taoism]] in [[Hong Kong]]''' is the religion of approximately 14% of the population.<ref>Hong Kong Government. ''[http://www.yearbook.gov.hk/2010/en/pdf/E18.pdf 2010 Yearbook - Religion]''. Retrieved on 23-09-2012.</ref>

Large local Taoist organizations include [[Ching Chung Koon]], [[Fung Ying Seen Koon]], Sik Sik Yuen ([[:zh:嗇色園]]), [[Yuen Yuen Institute]]. People often visit the temples of [[Wong Tai Sin Temple (Hong Kong)|Wong Tai Sin]], [[Che Kung Miu]] and [[Tin Hau temples in Hong Kong|Tin Hau temples]] during festivals.

